The paper deals with the representation and calculation of neutrosophic information using multi-valued logics. This topic is relevant to several sub-categories of computer science, including artificial intelligence (cs.AI) where multi-valued logics are used in reasoning and decision-making, logic (cs.LO) where the study of different logics is a central topic, machine learning (cs.LG) where uncertainty and ambiguity are important considerations, information theory (cs.IT) where entropy is a key concept, and data structures and algorithms (cs.DS) where the representation and manipulation of information is a core concern.
